# The app sets its login cookie with the Secure flag whenever
# ENVIRONMENT != dev (app/api/routers/auth.py), and browsers silently
# drop Secure cookies over plain HTTP — so login appears to do nothing.
# A real hostname (even a free wildcard-DNS one like <ip-with-dashes>
# .eu-cloud-xip.com / nip.io / sslip.io, which just resolves back to
# your own IP) lets Caddy get you a genuine, trusted Let's Encrypt
# certificate with zero extra config below — just put it in place of
# "your-domain-or-xip-hostname" and reload Caddy.
#
# See the "Hostname options" section of docs/vps-deployment.md if you
# only have a bare IP and no hostname at all.
# Canonical host: redirect www -> apex so there is exactly one origin.
# Without this, a visitor on https://www.kleeblatt.space sends Origin/Referer
# with a "www." host, but Caddy proxies Host: kleeblatt.space upstream, so the
# app's CSRF middleware sees mismatched hosts and 403s every POST (login,
# settings save, test-notification button) while GET/OAuth flows still work.
www.kleeblatt.space {
	redir https://kleeblatt.space{uri} permanent
}

kleeblatt.space {
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8000
}
